title: 9News Melbourne | Friday December 19 | Full Episode
description: Tonight, Brett McLeod leads the Melbourne Bulletin with the personal crisis facing Victorian Premier Jacinta Allan following her husband‚Äôs drink-driving charge in Bendigo, including exclusive reporting on the minor collision that preceded his breath test and expert political analysis on how this impacts the Premier's standing ahead of the new year. Our coverage continues with the dramatic release of seven Victorian men previously held in a Sydney counter-terrorism investigation and a major federal announcement from Prime Minister Anthony Albanese regarding a new National Gun Buyback scheme. We also take you to Bondi Beach, where the community held a poignant "paddle-out" ceremony to honor the victims of the recent terror attack, including the identification of the final victim, Tania Tretiak. Internationally, we report on the tragic private jet crash in North Carolina that claimed the lives of NASCAR legend Greg Biffle and his family, as well as the looming deadline for the full release of the Jeffrey Epstein investigation files. Closer to home, we cover the latest justice updates regarding Tony Mokbel and Jacob Hersant, safety concerns following beach brawls at Mordialloc, and a look ahead to the star-studded musical celebrations planned at the Melbourne Recital Centre to close out 2025.
